  ⎿  Error: Request failed with status code 403

⏺ Web Search("Flaticon API download SVG icons programmatically documentation")
  ⎿  Did 1 search in 19s                                                   

⏺ Yes! Flaticon has a proper API that would work perfectly for this. Here's
  what I found:

  Flaticon API

  Docs: https://api.flaticon.com/v3/docs/index.html

  How it works:

  1. Get an API key from https://pre-api.flaticon.com/ (your Pro account 
  should give you access)
  2. Search for icons - find icons by keyword
  3. Download as SVG - GET 
  https://api.flaticon.com/v3/item/icon/download/{id}?format=svg

  Key features:

  - Download in SVG, PNG, EPS, PSD
  - Change colors on monocolor icons via API (pass hex color)
  - Search by keyword, filter by popular/new
  - Auth via Bearer token

  For your Spanish game:

  You could absolutely do something like:
  // Fetch a "house" icon for "la casa"
  const response = await
  fetch('https://api.flaticon.com/v3/item/icon/download/123?format=svg', {
      headers: { 'Authorization': 'Bearer YOUR_API_KEY' }
  });
  const svgCode = await response.text();
  // Inject into the game

  Want me to help you set this up? You'd need to:
  1. Get your API key from the Flaticon portal
  2. We could add noun phrases with icon IDs
  3. Flash the SVG icon alongside the subject/object circles

