⏺ The structure of nfl_careers.json is an array of player objects with:

  {
    "name": "Player Name",
    "first_year": 2002,
    "last_year": 2002,
    "years": 1,
    "is_brady": false
  }

  Fields:
  - name: Player's full name
  - first_year: First year they appeared in the NFL (starting from 2002)
  - last_year: Last year they played
  - years: Total career length in years
  - is_brady: Boolean flag (true only for Tom Brady)

  The data tracks all players who were in the NFL from 2002 onwards, showing
   how long their careers lasted compared to Brady's.

